---
description: 
alwaysApply: true
---

- Ensure README.md exists at the project root at all times.
- The README.md must always include these sections in this order:
    1. Project title, course, and team
    2. Problem statement (one paragraph — what business question are we solving?)
    3. Technology stack (Python version, key libraries, LLM provider)
    4. Project folder structure (tree, one line per file/folder)
    5. How to set up locally (clone, pip install, .env, streamlit run)
    6. How to run tests (pytest command, expected output)
    7. Current implementation status — a table with columns:
       Module | Owner | Status (✅ Complete / 🔄 In Progress / 🔲 Not Started)
    8. Team roles table (member, role, files owned)
    9. Integration contracts (who produces what, who consumes it)
    10. Link to DEVELOPMENT_LOG.md for session-by-session progress
- Update README.md whenever:
    - A module changes status (not started → in progress → complete)
    - The folder structure changes
    - A new dependency is added
    - A new integration contract is established
    - Setup instructions change
- Do not generate or modify code in a way that affects any of the above
  without also updating README.md in the same edit session.
